<DocsLayout title="Administration - Infinity Metrics">
  <h1>Administration</h1>
  <p>
    Manage your Infinity Metrics installation, perform updates, and monitor
    system health.
  </p>

  <h2>System Status</h2>
  <p>Check the status of your Infinity Metrics installation:</p>
  <pre><code>sudo systemctl status infinity-metrics</code></pre>

  <h2>Updates</h2>
  <p>Update to the latest version:</p>
  <pre><code>sudo infinity-metrics update</code></pre>

  <h2>Backup</h2>
  <p>Create a backup of your analytics data:</p>
  <pre><code>sudo infinity-metrics backup</code></pre>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <p>
    Edit the configuration file at <code>/etc/infinity-metrics/config.yml</code
    >:
  </p>
  <pre><code>database:
  path: /var/lib/infinity-metrics/data.db
  backup_interval: 24h
server:
  port: 8080
  host: 0.0.0.0
security:
  api_key_required: true</code></pre>

  <h2>Logs</h2>
  <p>View application logs:</p>
  <pre><code>sudo journalctl -u infinity-metrics -f</code></pre>

  <h2>Maintenance Tasks</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Regular backups</li>
    <li>Monitor disk space</li>
    <li>Check for updates</li>
    <li>Review logs for errors</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Next: <a href="/docs/troubleshooting">Troubleshooting</a></p>
</DocsLayout>
